<paragraph id="B73836BB341EFF9AFF5CC473194F9381" blockId="5.[178,1085,321,402]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">
C o m m e n t 
<taxonomicName id="70874D38341EFF9AFEB2C47318089346" authorityName="FAGEL" authorityYear="1968" box="[348,544,321,342]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stenus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nitidiventris">
<emphasis id="85F3EAA9341EFF9AFEB2C47318089346" box="[348,544,321,342]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">Stenus nitidiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from Artvin (FAGEL 1967) and subsequently reported from numerous localities in 
<collectingCountry id="CF90762B341EFF9AFD0EC46C19199364" box="[736,817,350,372]" name="Georgia" pageId="5" pageNumber="274">Georgia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="D3164B4A341EFF9AFCAEC46D19E99365" author="PUTHZ V" box="[832,961,351,373]" pageId="5" pageNumber="274" pagination="5 - 6" refId="ref6242" refString="PUTHZ V. (1983): Einige Stenus - Arten aus dem Kaukasus und Elburs (Insecta: Coleoptera: Stpahylinidae). - Senckenbergiana Biologica 63 [1982] (5 - 6): 347 - 362." type="journal article" year="1983">PUTHZ 1983</bibRefCitation>
). The above male considerably expands the known distribution towards the west.
</paragraph>
